---
import '../styles/main.css';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Site Engineering - Chapter 1</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Century+Schoolbook&family=Roboto:wght@400;500&family=EB+Garamond:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>
  <body class="dark-mode site-engineering-background">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a> → <a href="/site-engineering">Site Engineering</a> → Chapter 1
      </nav>
      
      <h1>Site Engineering - Chapter 1: Technical Foundations</h1>
      
      <div class="content-section implementation-background">
        <h2>Code as Craft</h2>
        <p>
          "The best programs are written so that computing machines can perform them quickly 
          and so that human beings can understand them clearly." - Donald Knuth
        </p>
        
        <blockquote class="highlight">
          "Whatever you do, work at it with all your heart, as working for the Lord, 
          not for human masters." - Colossians 3:23
        </blockquote>
        
        <p>
          Engineering is not merely about making things work—it's about creating systems 
          that are maintainable, scalable, and elegant. Like the cathedrals of old, 
          our code should inspire both in its function and its form.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section solution-background">
        <h2>Modern Development Stack</h2>
        <h3>Our Technology Choices:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Astro.js</strong> - For static site generation and component architecture</li>
          <li><strong>React</strong> - For interactive components and state management</li>
          <li><strong>Three.js</strong> - For 3D visualizations and animations</li>
          <li><strong>D3.js</strong> - For data visualization and SVG manipulation</li>
          <li><strong>TypeScript</strong> - For type safety and developer experience</li>
          <li><strong>Bulma</strong> - For responsive CSS framework</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section experimental-background">
        <h2>Architecture Patterns</h2>
        <p>
          "Simplicity is the ultimate sophistication." - Leonardo da Vinci
        </p>
        <p>
          We follow the principle of progressive enhancement, building solid foundations 
          before adding complexity. Each layer should gracefully degrade, ensuring 
          accessibility across all devices and capabilities.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Component Strategy:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Atomic design methodology</li>
          <li>Props-driven configuration</li>
          <li>Semantic HTML structure</li>
          <li>CSS custom properties for theming</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <footer>
        <a href="/site-engineering" class="back-link">← Back to Site Engineering</a>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
